# skyscraper_watch config
# Paste your Discord channel webhook URL(s) here, then the next run will push alerts.
# Create one in Discord: Channel → Edit → Integrations → Webhooks → New Webhook → Copy URL
# Until at least one is set, changes are still detected and written to watch.log (no push).
#
# Copy this file to config.env and fill in the value(s). config.env is gitignored
# so the real webhook(s) never get committed.
#
# MULTIPLE WEBHOOKS — any of these work and can be mixed:
#   • repeat the WEBHOOK_URL line:
#       WEBHOOK_URL=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/aaa/...
#       WEBHOOK_URL=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/bbb/...
#   • use suffixed keys:
#       WEBHOOK_URL_2=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/ccc/...
#       WEBHOOK_URL_DEV=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/ddd/...
#   • comma-separate on one line:
#       WEBHOOK_URL=https://.../aaa/..., https://.../bbb/...
# Each webhook is alerted independently; one dead webhook won't stop the others.
WEBHOOK_URL=

# --- Auto-publish webhook messages (optional) ---
# If your webhook posts into an Announcement channel, setting a bot token here makes the
# watcher automatically click "Publish" for you (Discord's crosspost API) on every alert,
# so every server that FOLLOWS the announcement channel gets the message — no manual step.
#
# One-time setup:
#   1. Create a bot app: https://discord.com/developers/applications  (Bot → Reset Token).
#      No gateway intents needed — publishing is a single REST call, the bot never runs.
#   2. Invite it to the announcement channel's OWN server with View Channel + Send Messages
#      + Manage Messages (permissions=11264). Manage Messages is required because the
#      message author is the webhook, not the bot:
#        https://discord.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=YOUR_APP_ID&scope=bot&permissions=11264
#   3. Paste the bot token below. NOTHING is needed in the following servers.
# A non-announcement channel is simply skipped (logged), never errors the alert. Verify
# end-to-end with:  python3 skyscraper_watch.py --test
#DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=

# --- ETARC forum (Discourse) mirror — optional ---
# Posts the SAME change announcement as a reply to a forum thread, so it shows
# up in ETARC alongside your Discord channel. Uses a self-service User API Key
# (no admin key needed). To mint one:
#     python3 skyscraper_watch.py --authorize
# (needs `openssl`, already on the Pi; you approve it in your logged-in browser),
# then paste the three lines it prints below. Verify with:  --test
#DISCOURSE_BASE=https://forums.atlas-65.com
#DISCOURSE_USER_API_KEY=
#DISCOURSE_TOPIC_ID=9299

ARCHIVE_TRIGGER_URL=https://archive.goodguysfree.com/~api/trigger-crawl
ARCHIVE_TRIGGER_SECRET=
